[[File:ABii NATIONAL BANK TAKORADI.jpg|thumb|ABii National Bank, Takoradi]]

{{use dmy dates|date=April 2015}}

'''ABii National''' is a [[Savings and Loans Company]] in [[Ghana]] that provides financial service to the general public.

ABii National was established as a Savings and Loans company, as defined in Ghanaian law, in 2011. In February 2013, the [[Bank of Ghana]] granted the company a provisional license as a bank and in September of that year this was converted into a full license. By that time, it had six branches.<ref>{{cite news |title=Abii National Targets Full Banking Status |first=Samuel |last=Boadi |date=24 September 2014 |work=The Daily Guide |url=http://www.dailyguideghana.com/abii-national-targets-full-banking-status/ |accessdate=2015-04-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150203231753/http://www.dailyguideghana.com/abii-national-targets-full-banking-status/ |archive-date=3 February 2015 |dead-url=yes |df=dmy-all }}</ref> A seventh branch was opened at [[Takoradi]] in  March 2015, by which time the company had nearly 10,000 customers.<ref>{{cite news |title=BoG commends ABii National Savings And loans |date=21 March 2015 |work=The Spectator |url=http://www.spectator.com.gh/bog-commends-abii-national-savings-and-loans/ |accessdate=2015-04-20}}</ref>

Based in [[Accra]],<ref>{{cite web|title=Register of Non-Bank Financial Institutions as of December 2013 |publisher=Bank of Ghana |date=December 2013 |url=http://www.bog.gov.gh/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=84&Itemid=126 |accessdate=2015-04-20 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150321023422/http://www.bog.gov.gh/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=84&Itemid=126 |archivedate=21 March 2015 }}</ref> the company is a subsidiary of Tobinco.<ref>{{cite news |title=ABii National Expands It Tentacle To The Oil City |date=11 March 2015 |work=PeaceFM |url=http://business.peacefmonline.com/pages/finance/201503/235162.php |accessdate=2015-04-20}}</ref>

