'''Gull-Þóris saga''' ({{Audio|Is-Gull-Þóris saga.oga|listen}}) is one of the [[sagas of Icelanders]]. It tells the story of Gull-Þórir ('Gold-Thorir') Oddsson, a chieftain in [[Þorskafjörður]], and his dispute with Hallr his neighbour.

Þórir comes to Iceland with his father, Oddr skrauti. They settle in Þorskafjörður. Later Þórir goes raiding with Hyrningr the son of Hallr of Hofstaðir, and obtains gold in [[Finnmark]], where he defeats some dragons in a cave north of Dumbshaf. When the men come back to Iceland, Hallr wants to get a portion of the gold on behalf of his son, but Hyrningr is satisfied with his lot. This becomes a great controversy between Hallr and Þórir. Þórir kills both Hallr and Rauðr, his older son, but is reconciled with Hyrningr, who does not get involved in the dispute.

Þórir's wife is Ingibjörg daughter of Gill, who settled [[Gilsfjörður]], and their son is Guðmundr.

==External links==
*[http://www.sagadb.org/gull-thoris_saga Full text at the Icelandic Saga Database]

