{{noref|date=September 2016}}
The '''Kartvelian peoples''' are the ethno-linguistic groups of speakers of [[Kartvelian languages]]. "A Kartvelian people" may refer to:

* [[Georgians]]
** [[Svan people|Svans]]
** [[Zan people|Zans]]
*** [[Mingrelians]]
*** [[Lazs]]

The Svans and the Mingrelians, and the Lazs of Georgia are today commonly thought to be subgroups of the Georgians, and the term ''Kartvelian peoples'' is obsolescent (to refer to the modern-day peoples).{{Citation needed|date=September 2014}}

