{{bilateral|Kazakhstan-Netherlands|Kazakhstan|Netherlands}}
'''Kazakhstan–Netherlands relations''' refer to the bilateral relations between [[Kazakhstan]] and the [[Netherlands]]. The Netherlands has an embassy in [[Astana]].<ref name="NLembassy">{{cite web|title=Netherlands embassy in Astana|url=https://www.netherlandsworldwide.nl/countries/kazakhstan/about-us/netherlands-embassy-astana}}</ref> Kazakhstan has an embassy in [[The Hague]].<ref name="kzinNL">{{cite web|title=Kazakhstan embassy in The Hague|url=http://mfa.gov.kz/en/hague}}</ref>

__TOC__

==History==
{{expand section|date=July 2017}}

== Economic relations== 
There is significant trade between the two countries in agriculture, oil, chemicals and machinery sectors.<ref name="tradesectors">{{cite web|title=Relations the Netherlands - Kazakhstan|url=https://www.government.nl/topics/international-relations/overview-countries-and-regions/kazachstan|website=Netherlands government Rijksoverheid}}</ref>

The Netherlands is the largest source of foreign direct investment into Kazakhstan.<ref name="exportgovnlkz">{{cite web|title=Kazakhstan - Foreign Direct Investment and Foreign Portfolio Investment Statistics|url=https://www.export.gov/article?id=Kazakhstan-foreign-direct-investment-statistics|website=Export.gov}}</ref>

== State visits ==

In 2015, Dutch Prime Minister [[Mark Rutte]] met with [[Nursultan Nazarbayev]] in [[Astana, Kazakhstan]] and affirmed the Enhanced Partnership and Cooperation Agreement between the [[European Union]] and [[Kazakhstan]].<ref name="rutteinkz">{{cite news|title=Dutch PM Rutte lauds new EU-Kazakhstan partnership agreement|url=http://www.sandiegouniontribune.com/hoy-san-diego/sdhoy-dutch-pm-rutte-lauds-new-eu-kazakhstan-2015dec02-story.html|agency=EFE}}</ref>

