'''''Newspaper in Ukrainian''''' ({{lang-uk|Газета по-українськи}}) is an illustrated newspaper based in [[Kiev]] covering politics, economics, culture, sport, arts, and other different topics and aimed at the Ukrainian-language reader. It is published chiefly in Ukrainian but quotes in Russian are not translated. The newspaper has its own website - Gazeta.ua, where archives and additional information that is not included in the printed newspaper may be found. It has also editorial offices in [[Lviv]], [[Vinnytsia]], [[Poltava]], and [[Cherkasy]]. The owner of the newspaper is New Information Publishing Group Ltd. which also owns the magazine "Krayina" ("The Country").
==See also== [[List of newspapers in Ukraine]]
==External links== *[http://gazeta.ua/ ''Newspaper in Ukrainian'''s official website]
