'''Pulami''' is one of the core [[caste]]s of [[Magars]], an [[Indigenous peoples|indigenous]] [[ethnic group]] of [[Nepal]].  They are the largest indigenous group among the Magars.  Pulami are living everywhere in Nepal.  Major Pulami people are living in [[Udayapur District]].  They are mostly literate cast among Magar.  Pulami has two major Gotro{{clarify|date=February 2014}} popularly known as Jhingu and Dhalapi.  Liel Pulami{{who|date=February 2014}} is an example of Pulami.

