'''Radio Free Iraq''' (in [[Arabic language|Arabic]] إذاعة العراق الحرّ, transliteration Izaa'at al 'Iraaq al Hurr) was a 24-hour radio station broadcasting in [[Arabic language|Arabic]] from [[Prague]], [[Czech Republic]], and directed to [[Iraq]] and the Iraqi diaspora. It started its broadcasts on 30 October 1998<ref>[http://www.iraqhurr.org/]</ref> and was part of the programming of [[Radio Free Europe/Radio Liberty]] (RFE/RL), which is funded by the [[United States Congress]]. The radio station also ran an online edition which had regularly updated news and reports in Arabic.
The service ended on July 31, 2015,<ref>http://www.rferl.org/a/release-radio-free-iraq-signs-off-after-17-years-of-service/27161327.html</ref> after what RFE/RL characterized as a merger with [[Radio Sawa]] Iraq,<ref>http://www.radiosawa.com/p/432.html</ref> part of the Arabic-language Sawa service that replaced the [[Voice of America]] Arabic service.
