'''The Ghost''' is a [[Faroese people|Faroese]] [[synthpop|electropop]] duo consisting of Filip Mortensen on vocals and Urbanus Olsen on electronics.
Following their appearance at the [[Iceland Airwaves]] music festival, held in [[Reykjavík]], [[Iceland]], the duo received a recording contract with the British [[Sunday Best (music company)|Sunday Best]] record label.<ref name="DR">{{cite news | url=http://www.dr.dk/p3/musik/nymusik/2010/06/15/ny-musik-pa-p3-uge-23-2 | title=''Ny musik på P3: uge 23'' | first=Charlie | last=Alexander | language=Danish |trans-title=New Music on P3: week 23 | publisher=[[Danmarks Radio]] | date=15 June 2010 | accessdate= 23 May 2011}}</ref> The duo also appeared at the [[G! Festival]], held in [[Syðrugøta]], Faroe Islands, in 2009 and 2010.<ref>{{cite web | first=Matthew | last=Workman | url=http://faroepodcast.libsyn.com/faroe-islands-podcast-episode-59 | title=G! Festival 2010: Interview of Filip Mortensen of The Ghost | work=The Faroe Islands Podcast | date=11 August 2010 | accessdate= 24 May 2011}}</ref> In addition, they have performed as the warm-up band for [[The Wombats]], a British [[indie rock|indie-rock]] band; [[Ladytron]], an [[English people|English]] [[Electronic music|electronic]] band; and [[Vampire Weekend]], an [[Americans|American]] indie-rock band.<ref>{{Cite news | author = Erin-Madsen, Christian | title = ''The Ghost. G! Festival, Gøta, Færøerne, torsdag d. 23. juli 2009'' | url = http://gaffa.dk/anmeldelse/33694 | language= Danish | work = [[Gaffa (magazine)|Gaffa]] | accessdate= 23 May 2011 }}</ref>
In 2010, they released their debut album ''War Kids''.<ref>{{Cite news | author = Christensen, Simon | title = ''Charmerende færinger med identitetsløs elektrodebut'' |trans-title=Charming Faroese with Identity-less Electronic Debut | language= Danish | url = http://gaffa.dk/anmeldelse/41482 | work = [[Gaffa (magazine)|Gaffa]] | accessdate= 23 May 2011 }}</ref>
